        <section>
          <title>Elon Musk: the "Godfather" of Silicon Valley</title>
          <chapter>
            <paragraph>Why Apple should buy Tesla and appoint Elon Musk as CEO?
              Apple needs another Steve Jobs to reinvent itself and a combination of
              an operations executive such as Cook and a visionary such as Musk would be formidable.
              Musk is CEO of SpaceX and Tesla Motors, that developed electric vehicles and released first
              autonomous driving cars, and also Apple has been developing an electric vehicle.
              He probably would be interested in being part of Apple, if he were offered the CEO role.
              It could be another step of his successfull life. He started in PayPal, and so was part of the “PayPal Mafia”.</paragraph>
              <paragraph>What is PayPal Mafia? “PayPal Mafia” is used to denote a group of former PayPal
                employees and founders who founded and developed other tech companies, such as Tesla, SpaceX,
                Yahoo and Yelp. Three of them, have also become billionaires.</paragraph>
